1. Import the necessary libraries and read the provided CSVs as a data frame and perform the below steps.¶

Merge the provided CSVs into one data-frame.

Check a few observations and shape of the data-frame.

Round off scores to the nearest integers.

Check for missing values. Impute the missing values if there is any.

Check for duplicate values and remove them if there is any.

Keep only 1000000 data samples. Use random state=612.

Drop irrelevant features. Keep features like Author, Product, and Score.

# Selecting the data with products having more than 50 ratings and users who have given more than 50 ratings. And Reporting the shape of the final dataset.

    if n_users[i] <= 50:
        n_users = n_users[0:i]
        break
        
for i in range (len(n_products)):
    if n_products[i] <= 50:
        n_products = n_products[0:i]
        break

# Top 5 recommendations for test users using SVD based model

def get_top_n(predictions, n=3):
    # First map the predictions to each user.
    top_n = defaultdict(list)
    for uid, iid, true_r, est, _ in predictions:
        top_n[uid].append((iid, est))

    # Then sort the predictions for each user and retrieve the k highest ones.
    for uid, user_ratings in top_n.items():
        user_ratings.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
        top_n[uid] = user_ratings[:n]

    return top_n

top_n = get_top_n(test_pred, n=5)

top_n

# Top 5 recommendations for test users in user-user filtering model using KNNWithMeans

def get_top_n(predictions, n=5):
    # First map the predictions to each user.
    top_n = defaultdict(list)
    for uid, iid, true_r, est, _ in predictions:
        top_n[uid].append((iid, est))

    # Then sort the predictions for each user and retrieve the k highest ones.
    for uid, user_ratings in top_n.items():
        user_ratings.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
        top_n[uid] = user_ratings[:n]

    return top_n

top_n = get_top_n(test_pred, n=5)

top_n

# Top 5 recommendations for test users in item-item filtering model using KNNWithMeans

def get_top_n(predictions, n=3):
    # First map the predictions to each user.
    top_n = defaultdict(list)
    for uid, iid, true_r, est, _ in predictions:
        top_n[uid].append((iid, est))

    # Then sort the predictions for each user and retrieve the k highest ones.
    for uid, user_ratings in top_n.items():
        user_ratings.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
        top_n[uid] = user_ratings[:n]

    return top_n

top_n = get_top_n(test_pred, n=5)

top_n

10. In what business scenario you should use popularity based Recommendation Systems ?¶

Applicable business scenarios :

  1. New user of services such as online music, movies, tv shows, shopping websites, etc.
  2. An user who is using a particular service without logging in but has a login ID and password. For example, comparing prices of goods on Flipkart and Amazon without signing in.
  3. A user who has deleted profile history, if so the option was available on a particular platform (say, YouTube)
  4. It can be used complementarily with other recommendation system (content/collaborative), thereby showing products that are trending. This gives new opportunities to both the user and the service provider.
  5. Display of banner ads or in cases where resource constrains are there. Because popularity based recommendation systems consume less resource compared to other methods.

11. In what business scenario you should use CF based Recommendation Systems ?¶

Applicable business scenarios :

  1. Production recommendations by online shopping websites to users whose user history or item purchase history is available.
  2. Banks and lending platforms who are willing to give loan to users whos user of past loan history is available.
  3. Rental service platforms who want to lend products to regualr customers.
  4. Insurance companies who is willing to take opportunity of insurance renewal of user.
  5. Coupon or reward providing companies such as Cred can increase the activity of their users.

12. What other possible methods can you think of which can further improve the recommendation for different users ?¶

  1. Content based recommendation system
  2. Market basket analysis (items bought together - Assosiation rule mining)
  3. Hybrid recommendation systems
